The original code had interfaces that forced classes to implement methods that were not relevant to them, violating the Interface Segregation Principle (ISP). The refactored code separates the vehicle interfaces into specific types (IVehicle, IAirVehicle, IWaterVehicle) to ensure that classes only implement the methods they need.

