The original code had large interfaces that forced classes to implement methods that were not relevant to their responsibilities, violating the Interface Segregation Principle (ISP). The refactored code separates the `RestaurantWorker` interface into a more focused interface for restaurant tasks and a new interface for managerial tasks, allowing classes to implement only the methods that are relevant to them.

