The code previously forced operators to implement methods that were not relevant to their roles (e.g., a Driver implementing air navigation). By creating separate interfaces for `Flyable` and `Diveable`, we adhere to the Interface Segregation Principle (ISP), allowing classes to implement only the methods that are relevant to them.

